cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about a new classification loss function for neural networks. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on improving the loss function used to train neural networks. However, the paper also discusses experiments on a word language modeling task, which suggests relevance to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper introduces a new loss function that is designed to be computationally efficient, which could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
